Peru Stock Movers: Alicorp, Cerro Verde, Ferreyros, Relapasa

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-08-09T18:04:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-09/peru-stock-movers-alicorp-cerro-verde-ferreyros-relapasa.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1:27 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index rose for the first session in eight,
gaining 3.7 percent to 19,428.45. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index
gained 3 percent to 2,435.91.  Industrial stocks rebounded as U.S. stocks rose, said Edwin Paz, a Lima-based trader with Provalor SAB.  Corp. Aceros Arequipa SA (CORAREI1 PE), the Lima-based
steelmaker, jumped 6.3 percent to 2.35 soles. Refineria la
Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s Repsol YPF SA known
as Relapasa, rose 5.3 percent to 80 centimos after crude futures
advanced in New York.  Alicorp SA (ALICORC1)  (ALICORC1 PE), Peru’s largest
foodstuff maker, gained 5.3 percent to 5.37 soles.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1) 
(FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for Caterpillar Inc.,
rose 5.2 percent to 2.42 soles.  Copper, zinc and tin miners gained after metals advanced in
New York and  London .  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration
company, soared 8.3 percent to $1.18.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE),
the world’s fourth-largest tin producer, rose 7.5 percent to
3.28 soles. Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit
of Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc., gained 6.9 percent to
$38.50. Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based
zinc and silver mining company, rose 5.3 percent to 1 sol.  To contact the reporter on this story:
